interj.再会，再见；n.辞行，告别 【英】 interj. 再会,再见(goodbye);n.辞行,告别(saying goodbye) 【考】 panegyric : praise / valediction : farewell(颂词表示赞扬/告别 词表示告别)反义词：debut(初次 登场)-farewell performance(告别演 出) 【例】 make one's last farewells int. erj 再见 = goodbye; n 辞行; 告别话 【类】panegyric: praise = valediction: farewell颂词表示赞扬 = 告别话表示告别 【反】debut(v 首次登场)－farewell performance(告别演出) 【记】fare 交通费，旅行 + well→旅行顺风；fare 吃，费用，过活 + well→过好→再见时说的话 farewell (interj.)  late 14c., from Middle English faren wel, verbal phrase attested by c.1200 (see fare (v.) + well (adv.)); usually said to the departing person, who replied with good-bye. As a noun, by early 15c.
